p:
Genome editing, like the CRISPR-Cas9 system, could be used to implement in crops the resistance genes obtained by artificial evolution and to mutagenize directly host genes involved in recessive resistance to prevent interaction with viruses (
 Piron et al., 2010; 
 Chandrasekaran et al., 2016; 
 Pyott et al., 2016). However, the mutagenized plant genes could be involved in important biological functions, so the mutations may also have unexpected adverse effects in plant development or physiology.
